			<div class="section-header">Behaviour<br /></div>
			<div class="wiki-info">
				The Gallu cannot disturb salt piles while in its enraged state.
			</div>
			<br />
			<div class="section-header">Abilities<br /></div>
			<div class="wiki-info">
				The Gallu has three states it can switch to: "normal", "enraged", and "weakened". 
				By default, it starts in the normal state, where it behaves like a standard ghost. 

				<br /><br />
				It will change from the normal state to the enraged state or from the weakened state to the normal state:
				<ul>
					<li>instantly after burning a crucifix</li>
					<li>instantly after the end of the incense's blinding effect during a hunt</li>
					<li>
						after a certain amount of time equal to the duration of the last blinding effect of an incense after being affected by incense outside of a hunt
						instantly if no incense were used during any previous hunts
						<ul>
							<li>4 seconds if the Gallu was last blinded while in an enraged state</li>
							<li>5 seconds if the Gallu was last blinded while in a normal state</li>
							<li>6 seconds if the Gallu was last blinded while in a weakened state</li>
						</ul>
					</li>
					<li>2 seconds after stepping in salt if its current state is "normal"</li>
					<li>3 seconds after stepping in salt if its current state is "weakened"</li>
				</ul>
				
				<br />
				The state changes cannot be queued. For example, a weakened Gallu stepping in a second salt pile 1 second after stepping into the first one will not make it change into the enraged state 1 second after changing into the normal state.
			</div>
			<br />
			<div class="section-header">Hunt<br /></div>
			<div class="wiki-info">
				If a hunt ends while the Gallu is in its enraged state, it will instantly switch to the weakened state.

				<br /><br />
